{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QwqNrD37rXkKALRe5gEN73","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FCnT7rsZRKzsbEy46BvKZS","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/README.md","old_string":"## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.","new_string":"## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n\n## CLI\n\nThe package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.\n\n### Global install\n\n```sh\nnpm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n```\n\n### Quick start\n\n```sh\n# Create a board with three columns in the current directory\nkanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done\n\n# List columns and their card counts\nkanbamd columns\n\n# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)\nkanbamd add\n\n# List all cards\nkanbamd list\n\n# List cards in a specific column\nkanbamd list --column todo\n\n# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)\nkanbamd view\nkanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo\n\n# Move a card to another column (interactive)\nkanbamd move\n\n# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)\nkanbamd delete\n\n# Fuzzy-search cards\nkanbamd search \"login bug\"\nkanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n```\n\n### Board config\n\n`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"root\": \".\",\n  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n}\n```\n\nAll commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:\n\n```sh\nkanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list\n```\n\n### Command reference\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |\n| `columns` | List columns with card counts |\n| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |\n| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |\n| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |\n| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |\n| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |\n| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":273,"cache_read_input_tokens":50044,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":273},"output_tokens":58,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d22e3197-cafa-48fe-8f3e-bcff61c66b02","uuid":"d5a4a1bd-b59d-43c6-a6e4-80b7897da2d1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FCnT7rsZRKzsbEy46BvKZS","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspace/README.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d22e3197-cafa-48fe-8f3e-bcff61c66b02","uuid":"f660d936-1f3f-4947-8507-ce7888faa168","timestamp":"2026-05-03T16:55:55.847Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","oldString":"## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.","newString":"## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n\n## CLI\n\nThe package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.\n\n### Global install\n\n```sh\nnpm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n```\n\n### Quick start\n\n```sh\n# Create a board with three columns in the current directory\nkanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done\n\n# List columns and their card counts\nkanbamd columns\n\n# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)\nkanbamd add\n\n# List all cards\nkanbamd list\n\n# List cards in a specific column\nkanbamd list --column todo\n\n# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)\nkanbamd view\nkanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo\n\n# Move a card to another column (interactive)\nkanbamd move\n\n# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)\nkanbamd delete\n\n# Fuzzy-search cards\nkanbamd search \"login bug\"\nkanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n```\n\n### Board config\n\n`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"root\": \".\",\n  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n}\n```\n\nAll commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:\n\n```sh\nkanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list\n```\n\n### Command reference\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |\n| `columns` | List columns with card counts |\n| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |\n| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |\n| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |\n| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |\n| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |\n| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |","originalFile":"# @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n\nTypeScript package for managing Kanban boards stored as Markdown files with frontmatter and column folders.\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\nnpm install @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n```\n\n## Board Layout\n\n```txt\nboard/\n  todo/\n    fix-login.md\n  doing/\n  done/\n```\n\nEach card is a `.md` file:\n\n```md\n---\ntitle: Fix login\ntags:\n  - bug\norder: 1\npriority: high\n---\n\nMarkdown body.\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```ts\nimport { Kanbamd } from \"@alejandrocantero/kanbamd\";\n\ntype ProjectFields = {\n  priority?: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n};\n\nconst board = new Kanbamd<ProjectFields>({\n  root: \"./board\",\n  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"],\n  createRoot: false,\n  createColumns: true\n});\n\nawait board.init();\n\nconst card = await board.createCard(\"todo\", {\n  title: \"Fix login\",\n  tags: [\"bug\"],\n  body: \"OAuth callback fails.\",\n  frontmatter: {\n    priority: \"high\"\n  }\n});\n\nawait board.moveCard(\n  { column: \"todo\", id: card.id },\n  { column: \"doing\" }\n);\n\nawait board.reorderCard({ column: \"doing\", id: card.id }, 0);\n\nconst results = await board.searchCards({\n  query: \"logn callback\",\n  tags: [\"bug\"]\n});\n```\n\n## Memory Storage\n\n```ts\nconst board = new Kanbamd({\n  storage: \"memory\",\n  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n});\n\nawait board.init();\n```\n\n## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":92,"oldLines":3,"newStart":92,"newLines":76,"lines":[" - `order`"," "," Filesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.","+","+## CLI","+","+The package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.","+","+### Global install","+","+```sh","+npm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd","+```","+","+### Quick start","+","+```sh","+# Create a board with three columns in the current directory","+kanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done","+","+# List columns and their card counts","+kanbamd columns","+","+# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)","+kanbamd add","+","+# List all cards","+kanbamd list","+","+# List cards in a specific column","+kanbamd list --column todo","+","+# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)","+kanbamd view","+kanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo","+","+# Move a card to another column (interactive)","+kanbamd move","+","+# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)","+kanbamd delete","+","+# Fuzzy-search cards","+kanbamd search \"login bug\"","+kanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5","+```","+","+### Board config","+","+`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:","+","+```json","+{","+  \"root\": \".\",","+  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]","+}","+```","+","+All commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:","+","+```sh","+kanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list","+```","+","+### Command reference","+","+| Command | Description |","+|---|---|","+| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |","+| `columns` | List columns with card counts |","+| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |","+| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |","+| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |","+| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |","+| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |","+| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
