{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013DMbBCUJEutCNiiZ1iEm88","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me create a thorough overview report.\n\n## Comprehensive Project Overview\n\n### 1. Project Structure\n\nThe workspace contains a well-organized TypeScript package with the following directory structure:\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/                    # TypeScript source files\n│   ├── Kanbamd.ts         # Main class (core logic)\n│   ├── cli.ts             # CLI interface using Commander\n│   ├── index.ts           # Main exports\n│   ├── types.ts           # TypeScript type definitions\n│   ├── storage.ts         # Storage adapter pattern (filesystem & memory)\n│   ├── helpers.ts         # Utility functions\n│   └── errors.ts          # Custom error classes\n├── dist/                  # Compiled JavaScript output (generated)\n├── test/                  # Test suite\n│   └── Kanbamd.test.ts\n├── scripts/               # Build/release scripts\n│   └── release.mjs\n├── .github/               # CI/CD configuration\n│   └── workflows/release.yml\n├── package.json           # npm package metadata\n├── tsconfig.json          # TypeScript configuration\n├── biome.json             # Code formatting/linting config\n├── vitest.config.ts       # Test runner config\n└── README.md              # Project documentation\n```\n\n### 2. Package.json Contents\n\n**Project Info:**\n- Name: `@alejandrocantero/kanbamd`\n- Version: `1.4.3`\n- Type: ES Module (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- Description: \"Manage Kanban boards backed by Markdown files, frontmatter, and column folders.\"\n- License: MIT\n- Node requirement: `>=20`\n\n**Main Exports:**\n- **Primary export** (`.` path): `dist/index.js` with types at `dist/index.d.ts`\n- **CLI entry point**: `bin.kanbamd` → `dist/cli.js`\n\n**Build Scripts:**\n- `build`: TypeScript compilation (`tsc -p tsconfig.json`)\n- `format`: Code formatting with Biome\n- `lint`: Linting with Biome\n- `lint:fix`: Auto-fix linting issues\n- `typecheck`: Type checking only\n- `test`: Run Vitest\n- `release`: Node script for version releases\n\n**Core Dependencies:**\n- `commander` (^12.1.0) - CLI framework\n- `chalk` (^5.6.2) - Terminal colors\n- `@inquirer/prompts` (^7.10.1) - Interactive CLI prompts\n- `gray-matter` (^4.0.3) - Frontmatter parsing\n- `fuse.js` (^7.1.0) - Fuzzy search\n- `slugify` (^1.6.6) - URL-safe slugs\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- TypeScript, Vitest, Biome, @types/node\n\n### 3. README.md Overview\n\nThe README documents:\n- **Board Layout**: Kanban structure with column folders (e.g., `todo/`, `doing/`, `done/`)\n- **Card Format**: Markdown files with YAML frontmatter containing `title`, `tags`, and `order`\n- **API Usage**: Shows how to use the `Kanbamd` class programmatically\n- **Memory Storage**: Alternative in-memory storage option\n- **Reserved Frontmatter**: `title`, `tags`, `order` are managed by the library\n- **CLI Commands**: Complete reference for all 8 CLI commands (init, columns, list, add, view, move, delete, search)\n- **Board Config**: `.kanbamd.json` file for storing board settings (root, columns)\n\n### 4. Source Files and Architecture\n\n**Core Files:**\n\n1. **index.ts** - Main entry point\n   - Exports: `Kanbamd` class and all types/errors\n   - Exported types: `Card`, `CardFrontmatter`, `CreateCardInput`, `UpdateCardInput`, `SearchCardsOptions`, `ListCardsOptions`, etc.\n\n2. **Kanbamd.ts** - Main class (200+ lines)\n   - Constructor: Takes `KanbamdOptions` (root, columns, createRoot, createColumns, storage type)\n   - Public methods:\n     - `init()` - Initialize storage\n     - `listColumns()` - Get all columns\n     - `listCards(options?)` - List cards, optionally filtered by column\n     - `getCard(locator)` - Retrieve a specific card\n     - `createCard(column, input)` - Create new card\n     - `updateCard(locator, input)` - Update existing card\n     - `moveCard(locator, target)` - Move card between columns\n     - `reorderCard(locator, index)` - Change card order within column\n     - `deleteCard(locator)` - Delete a card\n     - `searchCards(options)` - Fuzzy search with filters\n   - Generic type parameter `T extends ExtraFrontmatter` for custom frontmatter fields\n   - Uses write queue to serialize write operations\n\n3. **types.ts** - Type definitions\n   - `Card<T>` - Card with id, fileName, column, frontmatter, body, timestamps\n   - `CardFrontmatter<T>` - Reserved (title, tags, order) + custom fields\n   - `CreateCardInput<T>`, `UpdateCardInput<T>` - Input types\n   - `CardLocator` - {column, id} identifier\n   - `SearchCardsOptions`, `ListCardsOptions` - Query options\n   - `StorageKind` - \"filesystem\" | \"memory\"\n   - `KanbamdOptions` - Configuration\n\n4. **storage.ts** - Storage adapter pattern\n   - `StorageAdapter` interface with methods:\n     - `init()` - Setup storage\n     - `listMarkdownFiles(column)` - List .md files\n     - `readCard(column, fileName)` - Read file content + timestamps\n     - `writeCard(column, fileName, content)` - Write file\n     - `moveCard(from, to)` - Move file between columns\n     - `deleteCard(column, fileName)` - Delete file\n   - `FilesystemStorage` - Implements adapter for actual filesystem\n   - `MemoryStorage` - Implements adapter for in-memory storage\n\n5. **helpers.ts** - Utility functions\n   - `toFileName(id)` / `toId(fileName)` - Conversions\n   - `createSlug(title)` - Generate URL-safe slugs\n   - `validateColumnName()`, `validateCardId()`, `validateTitle()`, `validateTags()`, `validateExtraFrontmatter()`\n   - `parseCardFrontmatter()` - Parse .md with frontmatter\n   - `stringifyCard()` - Serialize card to .md format\n   - `assertBaseFrontmatter()` - Type guard for frontmatter\n\n6. **errors.ts** - Custom error classes\n   - `KanbamdError` (base)\n   - `BoardRootNotFoundError`\n   - `ColumnNotFoundError`\n   - `CardNotFoundError`\n   - `DuplicateCardError`\n   - `InvalidFrontmatterError`\n   - `InvalidStorageConfigurationError`\n\n7. **cli.ts** - Complete CLI interface (550+ lines)\n   - Built with Commander.js\n   - Global options: `--root`, `--columns`\n   - Commands:\n     - `init` - Create board with .kanbamd.json\n     - `columns` - Show column stats\n     - `list` - List cards (interactive picker)\n     - `add` - Create card interactively\n     - `view` - Display card details (interactive)\n     - `move` - Move card to another column (interactive)\n     - `delete` - Delete card with confirmation (interactive)\n     - `search` - Fuzzy search with filters\n   - Uses `@inquirer/prompts` for interactive selection/confirmation\n   - Uses `chalk` for colored output\n   - Handles `.kanbamd.json` config file lookup (walks up directory tree)\n   - Auto-detects columns from directory structure if no config found\n\n### 5. CLI-Related Files\n\n**bin entry point:**\n- `package.json` declares `bin.kanbamd` → `dist/cli.js`\n- `/src/cli.ts` has shebang (`#!/usr/bin/env node`) and is 550+ lines of complete CLI implementation\n\n**Config file:**\n- `.kanbamd.json` - JSON file with `{ root: string, columns: string[] }`\n- Stored in project root, discovered via directory traversal\n\n**Config discovery logic:**\n1. Check for `.kanbamd.json` in current directory and walk up\n2. If found, load it and resolve root path relative to config location\n3. If not found, auto-detect columns by listing directories in current directory\n4. Can be overridden with CLI flags: `--root` and `--columns`\n\n### 6. Main Entry Points and Exports\n\n**For Library Use (`dist/index.js`):**\n```typescript\nexport { Kanbamd }                    // Main class\nexport * from \"./errors.js\"           // All 6 error classes\nexport type {\n  BaseFrontmatter,\n  Card,\n  CardFrontmatter,\n  CardLocator,\n  CreateCardInput,\n  ExtraFrontmatter,\n  KanbamdOptions,\n  ListCardsOptions,\n  NoReservedFrontmatter,\n  SearchCardsOptions,\n  StorageKind,\n  UpdateCardInput,\n}\n```\n\n**For CLI Use (`dist/cli.js`):**\n- Executable script with shebang\n- Entry point via `npm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd`\n- Provides `kanbamd` command\n\n### 7. Additional Configuration Files\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: NodeNext (ESM)\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output to `dist/`, source from `src/`\n- Generates declaration maps and source maps\n\n**biome.json:**\n- Formatter: 100-character line width, 2-space indent\n- Linter: Enabled with rules (no unused imports, arrow functions, block statements)\n- Organizes imports automatically\n- JavaScript-specific: double quotes, trailing commas, no semicolons\n\n**vitest.config.ts:**\n- Simple config, includes `test/**/*.test.ts`\n- Single test file: `test/Kanbamd.test.ts`\n\n### 8. Build Output\n\nThe `/dist/` directory contains compiled JavaScript:\n- `.js` files (transpiled code with source maps)\n- `.d.ts` files (TypeScript declarations with maps)\n- All 7 source modules compiled: Kanbamd, cli, index, types, storage, helpers, errors\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** This is a well-structured, production-ready TypeScript library with both programmatic (library) and CLI interfaces. It uses modern patterns (adapter pattern for storage, type-safe generics), comprehensive error handling, and follows best practices for both library packaging and CLI design. The CLI has full interactive support with config file discovery, and the library exports both the main class and all necessary types for type-safe usage."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68094eb4-e892-4d4e-90de-f1d86bf44291","uuid":"1d0f9457-0044-498e-9fd8-8c6bca5233f6","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:00:09.141Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the workspace at /workspace and give me a thorough overview of:\n1. The project structure (all files and directories)\n2. The contents of package.json\n3. Any existing README.md\n4. Any existing source files (src/ directory or similar)\n5. Any existing C