 createdAt: Date\n  updatedAt: Date\n}\n\ntype CardLocator = { column: string; id: string }\ntype CreateCardInput<T> = { title, tags?, body?, frontmatter? }\ntype UpdateCardInput<T> = { title?, tags?, body?, frontmatter? }\ntype ListCardsOptions = { column?: string }\ntype SearchCardsOptions = { query, columns?, tags?, limit? }\ntype KanbamdOptions = { root?, columns, createRoot?, createColumns?, storage? }\n```\n\n#### **storage.ts** - Storage Abstraction (168 lines)\nAbstract storage interface with two implementations:\n\n**StorageAdapter Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface StorageAdapter {\n  init(options): Promise<void>\n  listMarkdownFiles(column: string): Promise<string[]>\n  readCard(column, fileName): Promise<StoredFile>\n  writeCard(column, fileName, content): Promise<StoredFile>\n  moveCard(from, to): Promise<void>\n  deleteCard(column, fileName): Promise<void>\n}\n```\n\n**FilesystemStorage:**\n- Uses Node.js fs/promises for file operations\n- Stores cards as `.md` files in column folders\n- Manages directory creation with `mkdir({ recursive: true })`\n- Tracks file stats for createdAt/updatedAt\n\n**MemoryStorage:**\n- Maps columns to Maps of fileName -> StoredFile\n- Used for testing and ephemeral boards\n- No filesystem I/O\n\n#### **helpers.ts** - Utilities (110 lines)\n- `toFileName(id)` / `toId(fileName)` - Convert between formats\n- `createSlug(title)` - Generate URL-safe slug from title using slugify\n- `validateColumnName(column)` - Reject paths with `/`, `\\`, `.`, `..`\n- `validateCardId(id)` - Same path validation\n- `validateTitle(title)` - Non-empty string check\n- `validateTags(tags)` - Array of strings validation\n- `validateExtraFrontmatter(frontmatter)` - Reject reserved keys\n- `parseCardFrontmatter<T>(content)` - Parse markdown with gray-matter\n- `stringifyCard<T>(frontmatter, body)` - Serialize back to markdown\n- `assertBaseFrontmatter(data)` - TypeScript assertion for required fields\n\n#### **errors.ts** - Custom Errors (19 lines)\nAll extend `KanbamdError` base class:\n- `BoardRootNotFoundError` - Root directory missing\n- `ColumnNotFoundError` - Column doesn't exist\n- `CardNotFoundError` - Card file missing or invalid\n- `DuplicateCardError` - Slug conflict\n- `InvalidFrontmatterError` - Malformed frontmatter\n- `InvalidStorageConfigurationError` - Config issues\n\n### 4. BUILD & COMPILATION\n\n**TypeScript Compilation:**\n- **Input:** `src/**/*.ts`\n- **Output:** `dist/` directory with:\n  - `.js` - Compiled JavaScript (ES2022 target, ES modules)\n  - `.d.ts` - TypeScript declarations\n  - `.js.map` & `.d.ts.map` - Source maps for debugging\n- **Config:** `tsconfig.json` targets ES2022, Node.js module resolution\n- **Build command:** `npm run build` (runs `tsc -p tsconfig.json`)\n\n**npm Scripts:**\n```json\n{\n  \"build\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.json\",\n  \"format\": \"biome format . --write\",\n  \"lint\": \"biome check .\",\n  \"lint:fix\": \"biome check . --write\",\n  \"release\": \"node scripts/release.mjs\",\n  \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n  \"typecheck\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.typecheck.json\"\n}\n```\n\n**Package Entry Points:**\n- `main: \"./dist/index.js\"` - Library import\n- `types: \"./dist/index.d.ts\"` - Type definitions\n- `bin: { kanbamd: \"./dist/cli.js\" }` - CLI executable (has shebang)\n- `exports: { \".\": { import, types } }` - ESM export\n\n### 5. CLI CODE DETAILS\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Uses Commander.js for command parsing and routing\n- @inquirer/prompts for interactive multi-select/input/confirm\n- Chalk for terminal colors\n- Error handling via `run()` wrapper with ExitPromptError catch\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `resolveBoard(opts)` - Finds config file or detects columns, initializes Kanbamd instance\n- `findConfigPath(startDir)` - Walks up directory tree searching for `.kanbamd.json`\n- `detectColumns(dir)` - Lists non-hidden directories in a path\n- `printCardLine(card)` - Single-line card display\n- `printCardDetail(card)` - Multi-line card view with all metadata\n- `cardChoice(card)` - Formats card for inquirer select dropdown\n\n**Example Workflows:**\n```bash\n# Initialize\nkanbamd init --columns \"backlog,in-progress,done\"\n\n# Interactive add\nkanbamd add\n\n# Search with filters\nkanbamd search \"auth bug\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n\n# Move (interactive card picker if no ID given)\nkanbamd move my-card-id --to done\n```\n\n### 6. DATABASE SCHEMA (Markdown-based)\n\n**File Structure:**\n```\nboard/\n├── todo/\n│   ├── fix-login.md\n│   ├── add-auth-2fa.md\n│   └── update-docs.md\n├── doing/\n│   ├── refactor-api.md\n│   └── optimize-db.md\n└── done/\n    └── security-audit.md\n```\n\n**Card File Format (YAML Frontmatter + Markdown):**\n```markdown\n---\ntitle: Fix login regression\ntags:\n  - bug\n  - auth\norder: 1\npriority: high\n---\n\nOAuth callback fails on Firefox.\nNeed to check token refresh logic.\n```\n\n**Reserved Frontmatter Fields:**\n- `title` (string, required) - Card name\n- `tags` (string[], required) - Labels/categories\n- `order` (number, required) - Position within column (auto-managed)\n\n**Custom Frontmatter:**\nUsers can add any extra fields (e.g., `priority`, `assignee`, `deadline`) via TypeScript generics.\n\n**Metadata (from filesystem):**\n- `createdAt` - File creation time\n- `updatedAt` - Last modification time\n\n### 7. KEY DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `commander` | ^12.1.0 | CLI argument parsing |\n| `@inquirer/prompts` | ^7.10.1 | Interactive prompts |\n| `chalk` | ^5.6.2 | Terminal colors |\n| `gray-matter` | ^4.0.3 | YAML frontmatter parsing |\n| `fuse.js` | ^7.1.0 | Fuzzy search |\n| `slugify` | ^1.6.6 | URL-safe slug generation |\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- `typescript` ^5.4.5\n- `vitest` ^1.6.0 (test framework)\n- `@biomejs/biome` ^1.9.4 (linter/formatter)\n- `@types/node` ^20.12.12\n\n### 8. TESTING\n\n**Test Framework:** Vitest\n\n**Test File:** `/workspace/test/Kanbamd.test.ts` (200 lines)\n\n**Test Suites:**\n1. **Memory Storage Tests** - 4 test cases:\n   - Unique slug generation with auto-increment\n   - Card updates with frontmatter type safety\n   - Invalid input validation\n   - Card move/reorder operations\n\n2. **Filesystem Storage Tests** - 2 test cases:\n   - Directory creation and initialization\n   - Malformed markdown error handling\n\n**Coverage Areas:**\n- Slug generation and collision handling\n- Custom frontmatter support\n- Reserved key prevention\n- Search filtering by tags/columns\n- Order normalization\n- Move operations between columns\n- Error handling for missing files/columns\n\n### 9. RELEASE WORKFLOW\n\n**Release Process (scripts/release.mjs):**\n1. Parses release type (major/minor/patch/fix/premajor/etc.)\n2. Validates on `dev` branch with clean working tree\n3. Runs lint, typecheck, tests\n4. Bumps version in package.json using semver\n5. Runs `npm run build`\n6. Commits to `dev` and pushes\n7. Merges to target branch (default `main`)\n8. GitHub Actions CI/CD handles npm publish + GitHub release\n\n**GitHub Actions Workflow (.github/workflows/release.yml):**\n- Triggers on push to `main` or manual dispatch\n- Runs biome ci, typecheck, tests\n- Builds project\n- Publishes to npm (if not already published)\n- Creates GitHub Release tag\n- Auto-detects prerelease versions for npm tagging\n\n**Release Commands:**\n```bash\nnpm run release -- patch                           # Patch release\nnpm run release -- minor --dry-run                 # Dry run\nnpm run release -- preminor --preid beta          # Beta prerelease\n```\n\n### 10. CODE QUALITY TOOLS\n\n**Biome Configuration (biome.json):**\n- **Formatter:** 2-space indent, 100-char line width, double quotes\n- **Linter:** Recommended rules + require arrow functions + block statements\n- **Imports:** Auto-organize imports\n\n**TypeScript:**\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Source maps and declarations generated\n- Separate typecheck config (without emit)\n\n**Node.js Requirement:** >= 20\n\n### 11. ARCHITECTURE HIGHLIGHTS\n\n**Design Patterns:**\n- **Generic Class:** `Kanbamd<T extends ExtraFrontmatter>` allows typed custom frontmatter\n- **Storage Adapter Pattern:** Pluggable filesystem/memory backends\n- **Write Queue:** Sequential processing via Promise chain for concurrency safety\n- **Slug-based IDs:** Human-readable, collision-aware card identifiers\n- **Type Guards:** Runtime validation of required fields\n\n**Key Invariants:**\n- Order values are always positive integers starting at 1\n- IDs are URL-safe slugs (no `/`, `\\`, `.`, `..`)\n- Column names cannot contain path separators\n- Reserved frontmatter keys (title, tags, order) cannot be overridden by custom fields\n- All write operations maintain order consistency\n\nThis is a well-structured, production-ready library with comprehensive testing, a polished CLI, and clear separation of concerns between storage, validation, and business logic."}],"totalDurationMs":58103,"totalTokens":49826,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":145,"cache_read_input_tokens":45684,"output_tokens":3993,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":145},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":4,"output_tokens":3993,"cache_read_input_tokens":45684,"cache_creation_input_tokens":145,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":145,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":15,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":11,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
