2\t- `order`\n93\t\n94\tFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n95\t\n96\t## CLI\n97\t\n98\tThe package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.\n99\t\n100\t### Global install\n101\t\n102\t```sh\n103\tnpm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t### Quick start\n107\t\n108\t```sh\n109\t# Create a board with three columns in the current directory\n110\tkanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done\n111\t\n112\t# List columns and their card counts\n113\tkanbamd columns\n114\t\n115\t# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)\n116\tkanbamd add\n117\t\n118\t# List all cards\n119\tkanbamd list\n120\t\n121\t# List cards in a specific column\n122\tkanbamd list --column todo\n123\t\n124\t# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)\n125\tkanbamd view\n126\tkanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo\n127\t\n128\t# Move a card to another column (interactive)\n129\tkanbamd move\n130\t\n131\t# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)\n132\tkanbamd delete\n133\t\n134\t# Fuzzy-search cards\n135\tkanbamd search \"login bug\"\n136\tkanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n137\t```\n138\t\n139\t### Board config\n140\t\n141\t`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:\n142\t\n143\t```json\n144\t{\n145\t  \"root\": \".\",\n146\t  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n147\t}\n148\t```\n149\t\n150\tAll commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:\n151\t\n152\t```sh\n153\tkanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list\n154\t```\n155\t\n156\t### Command reference\n157\t\n158\t| Command | Description |\n159\t|---|---|\n160\t| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |\n161\t| `columns` | List columns with card counts |\n162\t| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |\n163\t| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |\n164\t| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |\n165\t| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |\n166\t| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |\n167\t| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |\n168\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aca4f6fe-3a5e-40b8-aa2d-1dcc85197f84","uuid":"a3337626-0668-4291-a583-857c4f96dabf","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:05:36.986Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"# @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n\nTypeScript package for managing Kanban boards stored as Markdown files with frontmatter and column folders.\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\nnpm install @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n```\n\n## Board Layout\n\n```txt\nboard/\n  todo/\n    fix-login.md\n  doing/\n  done/\n```\n\nEach card is a `.md` file:\n\n```md\n---\ntitle: Fix login\ntags:\n  - bug\norder: 1\npriority: high\n---\n\nMarkdown body.\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```ts\nimport { Kanbamd } from \"@alejandrocantero/kanbamd\";\n\ntype ProjectFields = {\n  priority?: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n};\n\nconst board = new Kanbamd<ProjectFields>({\n  root: \"./board\",\n  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"],\n  createRoot: false,\n  createColumns: true\n});\n\nawait board.init();\n\nconst card = await board.createCard(\"todo\", {\n  title: \"Fix login\",\n  tags: [\"bug\"],\n  body: \"OAuth callback fails.\",\n  frontmatter: {\n    priority: \"high\"\n  }\n});\n\nawait board.moveCard(\n  { column: \"todo\", id: card.id },\n  { column: \"doing\" }\n);\n\nawait board.reorderCard({ column: \"doing\", id: card.id }, 0);\n\nconst results = await board.searchCards({\n  query: \"logn callback\",\n  tags: [\"bug\"]\n});\n```\n\n## Memory Storage\n\n```ts\nconst board = new Kanbamd({\n  storage: \"memory\",\n  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n});\n\nawait board.init();\n```\n\n## Reserved Frontmatter\n\nThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n\n- `title`\n- `tags`\n- `order`\n\nFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n\n## CLI\n\nThe package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.\n\n### Global install\n\n```sh\nnpm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n```\n\n### Quick start\n\n```sh\n# Create a board with three columns in the current directory\nkanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done\n\n# List columns and their card counts\nkanbamd columns\n\n# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)\nkanbamd add\n\n# List all cards\nkanbamd list\n\n# List cards in a specific column\nkanbamd list --column todo\n\n# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)\nkanbamd view\nkanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo\n\n# Move a card to another column (interactive)\nkanbamd move\n\n# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)\nkanbamd delete\n\n# Fuzzy-search cards\nkanbamd search \"login bug\"\nkanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n```\n\n### Board config\n\n`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"root\": \".\",\n  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n}\n```\n\nAll commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:\n\n```sh\nkanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list\n```\n\n### Command reference\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |\n| `columns` | List columns with card counts |\n| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |\n| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |\n| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |\n| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |\n| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |\n| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |\n","numLines":168,"startLine":1,"totalLines":168}}}
